<h2><code>npm run</code> Reference</h2>
<li>You can run <code>npm run &#x3C;script> -s</code> to silence the default npm output (useful for calling a script within another script).</li>
<li>You can pass arguments to your scripts by passing <code>--</code> to <code>npm run</code>, followed by the arguments. Example: Given the script <code>"mocha": "mocha"</code>, you can run <code>npm run mocha -- --reporter xunit</code>. This effectively runs <code>mocha --reporter xunit</code>.</li>
]]></description><link>https://www.trackawesomelist.com/RyanZim/awesome-npm-scripts/week#2016-39</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.trackawesomelist.com/RyanZim/awesome-npm-scripts/week#2016-39</guid><pubDate>Mon, 26 Sep 2016 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[RyanZim/awesome-npm-scripts Sep 5th - Sep 11th, 2016]]></title><description><![CDATA[<h2>Task Runners</h2>
